  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Through interpretive coding, researchers can effectively categorize and organize information, enhancing the accuracy and efficiency of subsequent research tasks (St. Pierre & Jackson, 2014).",
    "Additionally, coding facilitates data sharing and collaboration among researchers, as it provides a common framework for understanding and interpreting data and contributes to the generation of transparent and reliable findings (Grimmer & Stewart, 2022).",
    "AI-driven technology can augment the qualitative researcher by performing tasks that are both fine-grained and scalable.",
    "Qualitative researchers in sociology and other disciplines have long recognized that AI-driven technologies, such as natural language processing (NLP)",
    "and machine learning, can automate and streamline research tasks, including extracting keywords, sentiments, or themes from large volumes of text (Do et al., 2022; Mohr 1998)."
  ],
